Data.event_text: 19 March  a few days prior to the state election, a video from September 2018 surfaced in which NSW Labor leader Michael Daley made comments about Asian immigration in Sydney. Daley said "Our young children will flee and who are they being replaced with? They are being replaced by young people from typically Asia with PhDs," and "So there's a transformation happening in Sydney now where our kids are moving out and foreigners are moving in and taking their jobs".

Data.event_text: 1214 April  After 25 years, Australia's Dirt n Dust Festival is held for the final time at Julia Creek, Queensland. Data.event_text: 16 May  Bob Hawke, Australia's 23rd Prime Minister, dies at the age of 89.

827 July  A biennial joint Australia-United States military exercise Talisman Saber 2019 is held.

Data.event_text: 21 August  The Victorian Court of Appeal dismisses George Pell's appeal to overturn his conviction for child sex offences.

29 August  An attempt to deport the Sri Lankan Tamil Nadesalingam family asylum seekers was thwarted by a last-minute injunction, forcing the plane carrying the couple and their children out of Australia to land in Darwin.
